{{Infobox person | name = Denise Pumain | image = [[File:Denise Pumain par Claude Truong-Ngoc octobre 2013.jpg|200px]] | caption = Denise Pumain in October 2013 (photo by [[Claude Truong-Ngoc]]) | birth_name = | birth_date = {{Birth year and age|1946}} | birth_place = | death_date = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (DEATH date then BIRTH date) --> | death_place = | nationality = French | other_names = | occupation = Geographer | years_active = | known_for = | notable_works = }}
'''Denise Pumain''' (born 1946) is a French geographer. Pumain specialises in urban and theoretical geography. She is a member of the [[Austrian Academy of Sciences]] and of the [[British Academy]].
==Early life and education== Pumain was born in 1946.<ref>{{cite web|title=Pumain, Denise (1946-)|url=https://viaf.org/viaf/16273/|website=Virtual International Authority File|accessdate=23 April 2018}}</ref> She studied geography at the [[École Normale Supérieure]] between 1965 and 1969 and received her doctorate in human sciences and literature in 1980.<ref name=ISCN>{{cite web|title=ISCN Inauguration|url=https://iscn.univ-lehavre.fr/event/iscn-inauguration/|website=iscn.univ-lehavre.fr|accessdate=23 April 2018}}</ref>
==Career==
She began teaching at the [[Paris 1 Pantheon-Sorbonne University]] in 1970.<ref name=britac>{{cite web|title=Professor Denise Pumain|url=https://www.britac.ac.uk/users/professor-denise-pumain|website=British Academy|accessdate=23 April 2018|language=en}}</ref> She became a researcher for the [[Institut national d'études démographiques]] in 1981 until 1986. In 1986, she became a Professor at the [[Paris 13 University]] before returning to the Paris 1 Pantheon-Sorbonne University to teach in 1989.<ref name=ISCN /> She also held the post of rector at the [[Académie de Grenoble]] between 2000 and 2001.<ref name=academy>{{cite web|title=Academy of Europe: Pumain Denise|url=http://www.ae-info.org/ae/Member/Pumain_Denise|website=www.ae-info.org|accessdate=23 April 2018}}</ref> In 1996, she founded the geography journal ''Cybergeo''.<ref name=ISCN />
She was awarded with a [[CNRS Bronze medal]] in 1984, decorated as a Chevalier of the Order of the [[Légion d'honneur]] in 1999 and decorated as an officer of the [[National Order of Merit (France)|National Order of Merit]] in 2009. Pumain also became a member of the [[Academia Europaea]] in 1995,<ref name=academy /> became a Corresponding Member of the [[Austrian Academy of Sciences]] in 2009 and became a Corresponding Fellow of the [[British Academy]] in 2012.<ref name=britac /> In 2010, she won the [[Vautrin Lud Prize]] and also received an Advanced Grant from the [[European Research Council]] to research different urban dynamics in cities across the world.<ref>{{cite book|last1=Longley|first1=Paul A.|last2=Goodchild|first2=Michael F.|last3=Maguire|first3=David J.|last4=Rhind|first4=David W.|title=Geographic Information Science and Systems|date=2015|publisher=John Wiley & Sons|isbn=9781118676950|page=356|url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=C_EwBgAAQBAJ&pg=PA356&lpg=PA356&dq=Denise+Pumain+biography&source=bl&ots=r5IzZv_6QE&sig=F3rCWSEc3VrO7ReSvfOIp3ynzCs&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwiD5ua7sNDaAhUCCMAKHaoDBl44ChDoATACegQIBxAB#v=onepage&q=Denise%20Pumain%20biography&f=false|language=en}}</ref>
