[[Image:Ohrid and Prespa lakes topographic map.svg|thumb|right|250px|Topographic map of the Prespa region]]
'''Prespa''' ({{lang-el|Πρέσπα}}, {{lang-mk|Преспа}}, {{lang-sq|Prespa}}) is a region shared between [[Greece]], [[Albania]], and the [[Republic of Macedonia]].<ref>Dr. Elli Louka, Water Law and Policy Governance Without Frontiers, Oxford University Press, 2008, {{ISBN|0199705887}}, p. 355.</ref> It shares the same name with the two [[Lake Prespa|Prespa lakes]] which are situated in the middle of the region. The largest town is [[Resen (city)|Resen]] with 9,000 inhabitants.  

== See also ==
* [[Prespes]], a municipality on the Greek side of the Prespa Lakes

